cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object pose estimation from RGB views. It also involves training a neural network using simulated data, which falls under the realm of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a single-encoder-multi-decoder network suggests that it may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) as it involves multiple objects and their orientations. Finally, the investigation of learned encodings and iterative refinement strategies may involve some graph theory (cs.GR) concepts.
